data.name: lblCloudCarouselAutoRotate.Help
data.value: Turn on auto-rotation of the carousel using either 'left' or 'right' as the value. The carousel will rotate between items automatically. The auto-rotation stops when the user hovers over the carousel area, and starts again when the mouse is moved off.

data.name: lblCloudCarouselAutoRotateDelay.Help
data.value: Delay in milliseconds between each rotation in auto-rotate mode. A minimum value of 1000 (i.e. one second) is recommended.

data.name: lblCloudCarouselFPS.Help
data.value: This is the approximate frame rate of the carousel in frames per second. The higher the number, the faster and smoother the carousel movement will appear. However, frame rates that are too high can make the user's browser feel sluggish, especially if they have an under powered machine. The default setting of 30 is a good tradeoff between speed and performance.

data.name: lblCloudCarouselMouseWheel.Help
data.value: If ticked, this will enable mouse wheel support for the carousel

data.name: lblCloudCarouselReflectionHeight.Help
data.value: Height of the auto-reflection in pixels, assuming applied to the item at the front. The reflection will scale automatically. A value of 0 means that no auto-reflection will appear.

data.name: lblCloudCarouselReflectionOpacity.Help
data.value: Specifies how transparent the reflection is. 0 is invisible, 1 is totally opaque.

data.name: lblCloudCarouselRotateSpeed.Help
data.value: This value represents the speed at which the carousel rotates between items. Good values are around 0.1 ~ 0.3. A value of one will instantly move from one item to the next without any rotation animation. Values should be greater than zero and less than one.

data.name: lblCloudCarouselXPos.Help
data.value: Horizontal position of the circle centre relative to the container. You would normally set this to half the width of the canvas width.

data.name: lblCloudCarouselYPos.Help
data.value: Vertical position of the circle centre relative to the container. You would normally set this to half the width of the canvas height.

data.name: litCloudCarouselBackgroundNote.Text
data.value:
You can specify the background of the canvas using color or image. For ex:
Example for background image:
background:url(/portals/0/images/canvasbg.jpg) no-repeat;

background:url(http://www.mysite.com/portals/0/images/canvasbg.jpg) no-repeat;

Example for background color:
background:#000000;
